{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Improve access to Parliament\u2019s work for people with learning difficulties",
        "additional_details": "We find it very hard to have a voice in Parliament when they want our views about the following\r\n \r\n\u2022 new laws\r\n\u2022 Government departments\u2019 work\r\n\u2022 Big issues that Government and Parliament should know about\r\n \r\nWe want the Government to work with people with learning difficulties led groups to look at how we can access information and tell the government what we think about:\r\n \r\n1) new laws\r\n2) Government departments\u2019 work\r\n3) Parliament\u2019s work \r\n4) big issues that Government and parliament should know about",
        "background": "We want the Government and Parliament to change so that we can participate in their work.\r\n\r\nWe want to change the law in the Equality Act so that this must happen.\r\n\r\nSee this petition in Easy Read: https://www.inclusionlondon.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Parliament-E-petition.pdf",
